    "retrievalTextLines": [
      "To ensure safety on site, you must distinguish between the mass of equipment and the force (weight) it exerts on supports.",
      "Weight (N) = Mass (kg) × 9.81 m/s².",
      "Mechanical advantage is gained by selecting the correct lever class: Class I (Fulcrum middle), Class II (Load middle), or Class III (Effort middle)."
    ],
    "questionText": "You are installing a heavy industrial transformer with a mass of 75 kg. \n\n1) Calculate the weight of the transformer in Newtons to determine the required strength of the floor fixings. \n2) You use a wheelbarrow (a Class II lever) to transport the transformer across the plant room. Identify which component—the Fulcrum, the Load, or the Effort—is positioned in the middle during this task.",
    "answerGuidance": [
      "1) 735.75 N (or 735.75 Newtons)",
      "2) The Load is in the middle"
    ],
    "hint": "For the calculation, multiply the mass by 9.81. For the lever, remember the 'FLE' rule for what is in the middle: Class I = F, Class II = L, Class III = E."
  }
}

